covered: Valid Request: Happy path verified by TC01 with 200 response and an array of Bundle objects.
Empty Response: Scenarios TC06 and TC24 cover empty arrays when no data is available or the database is empty.
Pagination: Offset/limit handling and boundary conditions covered by TC02, TC07, TC08, TC05, TC19, and TC26.
Query Parameters: Comprehensive testing of valid/invalid parameters including offset, limit, audit, extra parameter (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC18, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12).
Authorization: Missing/invalid token scenarios covered by TC13 and TC14 (401).
Error Handling/Resilience: Service unavailability (TC15), system error (TC16), and timeout (TC25) scenarios addressing error responses; invalid input scenarios (TC09, TC12) also covered.
Security: Injection attack scenario TC17 verifies input sanitization and safeguards against exposing sensitive information.
Backward Compatibility: TC21 ensures consistency with previously supported parameter combinations.
Performance/Concurrency: Large data performance (TC19), concurrent requests (TC20), and timeout behavior (TC25) address performance considerations.
Data Filtering Scenarios: Partial dataset (TC23) and substring search (TC27) validate filtering behavior.
Audit Detail Variants: TC03 and TC04 verify full vs minimal audit information in responses.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate-limiting/throttling under high request volume.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional requests.
Authorization Depth: No test for 403 Forbidden scenarios where a user is authenticated but lacks permissions.
Edge Case Not Found: No explicit test for 404 Not Found on non-existent resources (where applicable).
UI Accessibility Depth: TC22 covers screen-reader accessibility but broader accessibility testing across devices/assistive technologies could be expanded.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling behavior and appropriate 429 responses under burst traffic.
Add caching header validation tests (ETag, Cache-Control) and support for conditional requests.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover authorization failures due to insufficient permissions.
Add 404 Not Found edge-case tests for non-existent resources or invalid paths where applicable.
Expand accessibility testing beyond a single UI client to cover additional assistive technologies and scenarios.
Extend pagination coverage with additional last-page scenarios and varying dataset sizes to ensure robust pagination behavior.
